eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

Patients with neuroblastoma who do not have measurable disease but have iodine-131 -
             meta-iodobenzylguanidine positive (MIBG+) evaluable disease are eligible.

For patients with unresected head and neck tumors other than SCC of oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, or hypopharynx, there is no requirement for induction chemotherapy prior to protocol chemoradiation
Participants must be able to swallow oral medications
Resident in metropolitan Washington, D.C., greater New York City, or southern California; no short-term visitors
Any history of second or third degree heart block (may be eligible if currently have a pacemaker)

Diagnosis of secondary acute myeloid leukemia, myelodysplastic syndrome, chronic
             myelogenous leukemia, or secondary thrombocytosis.

Patients with a history of other invasive malignancies, with the exception of non-melanoma skin cancer, are excluded if there is any evidence of other malignancy being present within the last 5 years; patients are also excluded if their previous cancer treatment contraindicates this protocol therapy
Subjects who have received prior solid organ transplantation are not eligible

The following assessments are required within 14 days prior to registration: sodium (Na), potassium (K), chloride (Cl), glucose, calcium (Ca), magnesium (Mg), and albumin; Note: patients with an initial magnesium < 0.5 mmol/L (1.2 mg/dl) may receive corrective magnesium supplementation but should continue to receive either prophylactic weekly infusion of magnesium and/or oral magnesium supplementation (e.g., magnesium oxide) at the investigator’s discretion

groups.description: Patients undergo standard Mohs micrographic surgery to excise the remaining BCC tissue.
groups.name: Arm II (standard carel)

groups.description:
Induction: up to 2 cycles with cytarabine and daunorubicin/idarubicin, followed by the experimental drug quizartinib
Consolidation: up to 4 cycles of cytarabine followed by the experimental drug quizartinib and/or hematopoeitic stem cell transplant
Maintenance: up to 12 cycles with the experimental drug quizartinib
groups.name: Induction and consolidation chemotherapy plus quizartinib

outcome_measures.measure: The percent change in spleen volume based on MRI at the end of Cycle 3 relative to baseline

outcome_measures.time_frame: Cycle 1: multiple timepoints. Thereafter, single samples at designated cycles
